cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV. 

The paper presents a memory augmented neural network for natural language understanding, which suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. However, given the focus on natural language tasks, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category. Additionally, the use of neural networks and memory augmentation suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely categories. The use of memory and attention mechanisms also suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as a possible category. Finally, the paper includes a task related to document sentiment analysis, which suggests cs.CV (Computer Vision) as a possible category due to the overlap between natural language processing and computer vision tasks.
